summary: This is a travel authorization email from the DOJ's E2 travel system, approving a trip for a witness interview related to the Epstein investigation. The traveler is scheduled to go to Pensacola, FL on February 19-20, 2020.

events.title: Scheduled Witness Interview Travel
events.description: Travel is authorized for a witness interview related to the Epstein investigation in Pensacola, FL.

keyFacts: A travel authorization (ID 11063042) was approved on February 14, 2020, for the Epstein investigation.
The purpose of the travel was for a witness interview, coded as 'R20NYS13403 - Epstein Investigation - Witness interview'.
The destination was Pensacola, FL, with travel dates scheduled for February 19-20, 2020.
The authorization was processed through the U.S. Department of Justice's E2 travel system, indicating official government business.
The document shows active investigative work related to the Epstein case was ongoing in early 2020.
